<paragraph id="14C5AA09DFE4F8A930663983D32994A5" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">
Worldwide, with about 1,350 species. The number of genera admitted varies greatly depending on the authors. In this work, the species are arrayed in nine genera following Maddison (2012: 570): 
<taxonomicName id="2AE17F30B1BBE95F85DDE5141A621EDB" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1868" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amerizus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="342" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FCED4685F9253272973A2B5A07098FB5" italics="true" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Amerizus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 
<taxonomicName id="421433C63C1D9C69EA9ED718E13FFD2F" authorityName="des Gozis" authorityYear="1886" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Asaphidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="342" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1F57B0B939FB52D4A2B378F021E6F758" italics="true" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Asaphidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
